<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Pretty cool, but...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Draigon">Draigon</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:38 a.m. 20/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Pretty cool, but...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/veeshan.cgi?read=8" TARGET=_self>Guides: Finding a guild, Creating a guild, Guild Leadership and more...</A> (Brimstone)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Some of those guides you need to keep in mind it's not a strict rule. More of a opinion. One example would be:

<P><BLOCKQUOTE><I>
<BR>If you are not a people person, turn away from guild leadership now. RUN! If you cannot mask your frustration, hide your
<P>fears, conceal your annoyed feelings, etc., turn away. To be a GOOD leader, you need to set aside many of your opinions,
<P>many of your stereotypes, your own wants and needs and desires, and focus 100% on the people you are leading.</I></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>I really don't agree with that. It's as though you are a political leader.. like a president of the US. For my guild, I like to be just another member. To tell them of my frustrations like a group of friends... here they are suggesting you act like the leader of a nation and only show your good side. Just a note, thats all... to keep in mind they might be wrong on some things. I'm sure if I were trying to start up an all paladin guild that this method would be good.
<P>-Draigon
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
